  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Duties & Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible for the bidding information collection work</li><li>Prepare all bill of quantity for the whole project and vendor report</li><li>Prepare monthly progress report and progress claim to Consultant</li><li>Call for supplier/subcontractor quotation and compare with tender details</li><li>Verify subcontractors’ and suppliers’ claim and prepare interim payment certificate</li><li>Responsible for the quality/accordance to the specification of the works</li><li>Check all new drawings for variations works</li><li>Responsible for collecting, sorting and checking of bidding calculation of quantities</li><li>Organize subcontract price and negotiations</li><li>Compile bidding quotations and submit to department manager to review</li><li>Perform all other duties or tasks as assigned by immediate superiors.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Quantity Surveying or equivalent.</li><li>Minimum 1 years relevant experience in Singapore construction, preferably with PUB.</li><li>Proficient in MS Office.</li><li>Experience in Pipeline services.</li><li>Able to work independently with minimum guidance and under pressure to meet tight deadlines.</li></ul>",
